EDITH MONACO, BY NEXT FRIEND, ET AL., PLAINTIFFS, v. ABRAHAM KIRSCHNER ET AL., DEFENDANTS. Decided July 10, 1928.

Before Justices Mixture, Black and Campbell.

For the plaintiff, Palmer & Cooper. For the defendants, McDermott, Enright & Carpenter. Per Curiam.

The motion in the above-entitled cause to vacate the service of the summons upon the defendant, after due consideration by the court, is denied.
